currentStatement

public org.openrdf.model.Statement currentStatement()
                                             throws FStatementInput.InvalidUserInputException
Returns the current statement if it is complete (i.e., user input has been made), or null if the form does currently not represent a valid statement. This implementation relies on getCurrentSubject(), getCurrentPredicate(), and getCurrentObject() and should work if all of them are re-implemented properly in the subclass. Still, in some cases the developer may opt to completely re-implement this method.

Throws:
FStatementInput.InvalidUserInputException

getInitClone

public abstract FStatementInput getInitClone(java.lang.String id,
                                             boolean cloneInitSubj,
                                             boolean cloneInitPred,
                                             boolean cloneInitObj)
Clones the current object, while possibly copying the init subject, predicate, and object according to the configuration. The current values are not considered, i.e. will be blank for the cloned object.

Parameters:
id - the FComponent id for the new object
cloneSubj - keep (true) or discard (false) the init subject
clonePred - keep (true) or discard (false) the init predicate
cloneObj - keep (true) or discard (false) the init object
Returns:
